title: For Sale:  New Tipton 216411 Deluxe 1-Piece Carbon Fiber Cleaning Rod 22-26 Cal 26"
postcontent:
*** NO TRADES ***

New Tipton 216411 Deluxe 1-Piece Carbon Fiber Cleaning Rod 22-26 Cal 26"

$23 (FIRM)

Product Description

Carbon fiber is well-suited to the tough tasks assigned to cleaning rods. It combines the best features of stainless steel and coated cleaning rods, then adds valuable properties of its own. Stainless steel rods can scratch or wear barrels if they're used carelessly - though they won't pick up potentially damaging small abrasive particles. "Coated" rods get part of the job done - they keep the stainless steel shaft from damaging your barrel's rifling, but the coating will pick up small abrasive particles, which means you're effectively running finegrit sandpaper through your bore. Carbon fiber rods are the best of both: the carbon fiber can't scratch your bore like stainless steel, and they won't embed like coated rods. Plus, Carbon Fiber rods can be bent to an extreme degree and return to their original straightness. During Operation Iraqi Freedom, US military armorers called on Tipton to provide cleaning rods that would clean service rifles in demanding conditions. It made sense to us: Carbon fiber is an ideal material for cleaning rods. We call these cleaning rods "deluxe" because they feature an ergonomically designed handle that spins on two sets of ball bearings - the result is a cleaning rod that smoothly follows the rifling both pushing and pulling, even while under pressure. The "shank-through" construction also allows the user to apply "reasonable" hammer blows to the end of the cleaning rod to get a tight patch through a bore. Available in four diameters and six lengths to fit most rifles, pistols, and shotguns. Rifle and handgun rods are threaded for 8-32 accessories, except 17 caliber and 20 caliber rods which are threaded 5-40. Shotgun rods are threaded 5/16"-27.
Hang hole for easy storage. Also allows for reasonable hammer blows to clear a stubborn patch.
Two sets of high quality bearings that won’t bind under pressure and allows the shaft to follow the rifling.
Comfortable ergonomic shape. Handle remains fixed in your hand while the shaft rotates on the bearings to follow rifling.
Shank-through construction for working tight patches.
Carbon fiber shaft won’t embed particles that could damage your rifle bore.

Product Specifications

title: For Trade:  WTT New Adcor Defense B.E.A.R. Elite Piston AR15 16" Upper for LR-308 Upper
postcontent:
The ADCOR B.E.A.R. was a finalist in the discontinued US Military Individual Carbine trials for the new AR platform that will be replacing/upgrading the M4, along with the FN MK16 SCAR-L, Remington ACR, Colt APC, and the Heckler and Koch HK416. 


* FN Manufacturing 1:7 twist, hammer-forged, double chrome-lined barrel with M249 rifling profile for long life and exceptional accuracy 

* Cerro Forge keyhole upper receiver

* Forward placed, reversible/ambidextrous charging handle - Simple design allows the operator to keep his or her strong hand on the firearm and use the other hand to clear the rifle. Ambidextrous handle detaches easily without special tools and returns to locked position once used. It folds forward, recessed, and easily swings back out in a single motion. Non-reciprocating handle only engages when the operator charges or clears. 

* Patented ejection port dust wiper on carrier (See Below) 

* Gas piston system with multi-position regulator - (Patent # REDACTED8) A gas-driven piston incorporated into the upper half of the forward rail system never touches the barrel. 

* Free-floating barrel - for increased accuracy 

* Two-piece keyed 7075 quad rail system - not 6061 

* Tool-less field strip design 


ADCOR patented their Full Auto BCG's exclusively. They have a special, one of a kind dust plate that keeps the inside of the AR's clean, even with the dust cover open. The spring-loaded dust shield mounted on the bolt carrier allows the bolt carrier to return to ready position; the port dust wiper moves into the ejection port opening flush with the inside geometry of the upper receiver. Withstands temperature extremes because of the highly durable, self-lubricating polymer shield. 

In 2010, H.P. Laboratories ran the ADCOR AR's through a torture test that included being submerged in water, buried in sand and 6,000 rounds were fired in 120 round cycles, and the guns were lubricated and allowed to cool after 600 round intervals. During the tests, no parts had to be replaced and there were no jams, stoppages, or malfunctions of any kind. Following this, the B.E.A.R. was able to shoot a .88 MOA group at 100 yards with 69-grain match ammo. 

B.E.A.R. (Brown Enhanced Automatic Rifle) models from Adcor Defense feature a patent-bearing, gas piston system with a free-floating barrel for increased accuracy. This is due to the piston's incorporation into the upper half of the forward rail system - so it never touches the barrel. Extremely close machine tolerances eliminate the need for piston rings. With a tool-less field strip design, a B.E.A.R. requires nothing more than a firing pin to disassemble, yet remains strong. The piston's cyclical rate for a controlled rate of fire adjusts with a turn of the gas plug located in the front piston assembly. Because diminished heat reaches the upper, hot gases and carbon particulates are prevented from entering the receiver, lubricant lasts longer and maintenance is simplified. Due to superior design, the B.E.A.R. has no carrier tilt and low fouling of the chamber and action. 

Trade for LR-308 upper (preferably piston model) with 20" or larger barrel +/- cash if necessary. I can also ship and receive through my local gunshop, if preferred. 

NO KNIVES, LIGHTS, TRAINING COURSES, LOWBALL OFFERS, etc - I WILL NOT RESPOND

postcontent:

It bears all matching assembly numbers except for the bolt, which matches itself. The serial number puts this rifle very early in the production of Type 38s. The wood is in good condition with some scuffs and bumps, and the handguard has a crack at the barrel band. The metal is also in good condition with some bluing left. The bore is very worn, but rifling is still visible. It is missing the cleaning rod.

I am asking $275 or best offer.

title: For Sale:  Superb Carcano M41, 6.5x52 with Bayonet and Accessories
postcontent:
I've had this rifle for over 30 years and it's without a doubt the nicest Carcano I've ever had and I have owned a number of them over the years. The 6.5x52 Carcano round is powerful and accurate with similar performance to the 6.5x55 Swedish Mauser round. 

The M41 is an improvement of the original Model of 1891. It's somewhat shorter yet still full rifle length. It's built stronger and has much improved sights. It's began production in 1941 and continued to near the wars end. Almost immediately after the war some of the issued M41's were sent back to the arsenal and underwent a full reconditioning for export and this rifle is one of those.

It's in superior condition. The blued steel finish is at least 98%, and the wood is excellent as well with only the most minor of handling marks. Bore is in great shape and everything functions as it should. There are only two numbers on the rifle (barrel/receiver and stock) and they both match. The bolt is not numbered and this isn't unusual at all with Carcanos. When you look at this rifle it basically appears new, and I think you'd be hard pressed to find a better example.

Rifle comes with a scarce and original leather sling in excellent shape as well as an original lead oiler bottle and Carcano screwdriver tool.

Then there is a bayonet in excellent condition. Finally there are 2 brass Carcano clips and 18 rounds of original Italian wartime production ammo.

Bottom line is that this is a wonderful collectible that you can take out and have some fun with. You'll certainly get some looks and probably a few questions from curious onlookers out at the range since M41's just aren't seen that often.

Price $475.00 with pickup in the Brandon area. I won't ship as it's just too much trouble to do so today. Buyer must be at least 18 years old and a Florida resident. 

Thanks for looking
